page.title: 14ANNUAL EVENTS 1
page.content: The Grand Western Archery Society, now over 100 years old, holds the annual championships on the Lawns below the castle. It is at this event that archers from all parts of Britain gather to compete. Dunster Show, an agricultural show, is one of the leading events of its kind in the West Country and takes place in August. Dunster Show is more than 130 years old. Dunster Horticultural Society holds its annual Flower and Vegetable Show in the Memorial Hall in late July. West Somerset Hunt meets at Dunster Castle on Boxing Day and the Yarn Market is the venue for frequent meets of the Minehead Harriers.
